- `progressStyle: "circular"` is not exported at all. The dashboard supports circular progress and the task requires the exported widget to bake in and visually match current settings; exported HTML only renders the timer or linear progress, so circular-progress configurations lose an entire visual feature.
- Per-breakpoint export is only partially honored. The generator emits media-query CSS for styles, but DOM/runtime choices (visible units, labels, header/subheader, animation style, progress style, completion settings) are frozen from the currently active config. Since the store allows per-breakpoint config changes broadly, exports can fail to match desktop/tablet/mobile settings beyond basic styling.

Security: generated CSS interpolates config strings directly into a `<style>` block and immediately previews the result via `srcDoc` with scripts enabled. If untrusted config can enter the store, this creates an HTML/script injection path. This should be escaped or constrained before rendering/exporting.

Next actions:
1. Fix redirect handling so same-tab redirects fall back directly from blocked top navigation to `window.open(..., "_blank")`.
2. Add circular progress markup/CSS/runtime updates matching `CircularProgress.tsx`.
3. For per-breakpoint mode, either constrain it to documented style-only settings or generate responsive DOM/runtime behavior for all supported per-breakpoint settings.- Same-tab redirect fallback is implemented incorrectly. The requirement says to attempt `window.top.location.href` and, if sandboxing blocks it, fall back to `window.open(url, "_blank")`. The exported script instead falls back to `window.location.href`, which will usually navigate only the iframe and never open the promised new-tab fallback. This breaks a required completion behavior.
- `progressStyle: "circular"` is not exported at all. The dashboard supports circular progress and the task requires the exported widget to bake in and visually match current settings; exported HTML only renders the timer or linear progress, so circular-progress configurations lose an entire visual feature.
- Per-breakpoint export is only partially honored. The generator emits media-query CSS for styles, but DOM/runtime choices (visible units, labels, header/subheader, animation style, progress style, completion settings) are frozen from the currently active config. Since the store allows per-breakpoint config changes broadly, exports can fail to match desktop/tablet/mobile settings beyond basic styling.

Security: generated CSS interpolates config strings directly into a `<style>` block and immediately previews the result via `srcDoc` with scripts enabled. If untrusted config can enter the store, this creates an HTML/script injection path. This should be escaped or constrained before rendering/exporting.

Next actions:
1. Fix redirect handling so same-tab redirects fall back directly from blocked top navigation to `window.open(..., "_blank")`.
2. Add circular progress markup/CSS/runtime updates matching `CircularProgress.tsx`.
3. For per-breakpoint mode, either constrain it to documented style-only settings or generate responsive DOM/runtime behavior for all supported per-breakpoint settings.